{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f2516a5f-c698-4d2b-8fee-866f2374e673","content":"The working directory appears to be empty. There are no files here — no source code, no log files, and no CLR activation logs to analyze.\n\n**About your question:** CLR activation logs (e.g., from `COREHOST_TRACE` or Fusion Log Viewer) relate to **assembly loading and host startup**, not runtime exceptions like `NullReferenceException`. These are two different issues:\n\n- **CLR activation logs** → diagnose missing SDKs, framework resolution failures, assembly binding issues.\n- **NullReferenceException** → a code bug where you dereference a `null` object.\n\n**To debug your NullReferenceException, I'd recommend:**\n\n1. Check the **stack trace** — it tells you exactly which line threw.\n2. Look at the object being accessed on that line and trace why it's `null`.\n3. Common causes: uninitialized dependency injection, missing config values, or a service not registered in `Program.cs`/`Startup.cs`.\n\nIf you can share your **source code**, **stack trace**, or **log files**, I can help pinpoint the bug. Would you like to provide those?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d8e3d480-0342-4380-8686-680ff71498f9","outputTokens":265,"requestId":"7842:8A8EB:1D8F3AF:20EC73D:69FA9AF9"},"id":"ebc1012f-9ed5-4efb-9277-b27c4be6d1a4","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:36:01.431Z","parentId":"036beaaa-e535-4af6-a3ac-c734716201a9"}
